title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H2 – Feb 9 2022
itunes:title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H2 – Feb 9 2022
description:
Fauci joins the big election pivot, The View lags behind. Crime's so bad, they're locking up Rev. Al's toothpaste. Buck says about his own corner drugstore, "Let me tell you, they're locking up the Buckster's toothpaste, too." Clay says, "You know things are bad when Al Sharpton is demanding more police presence and more security." Fabulous CBC interview with a Canadian trucker. Buck refuses to let the Fauciites get away with it. He also promises that, in addition to never being grateful, "I'm going to hound Fauci for the rest of his days in public life as much as I can." What will New York look like now that the governor is loosening some restrictions? C&B talk to callers.
